Key Match Events: Donte DiVincenzo scored 11 points in the second quarter to help the Timberwolves dominate the period 32-12.
A 3-pointer from DiVincenzo gave the Timberwolves a 108-103 lead with three minutes remaining.
DiVincenzo hit the crucial free throw that ultimately sealed the victory.
Post-Match Reflections: Wembanyama finished with 34 points on 30 shots in the loss.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Timberwolves held off the gritty San Antonio Spurs on Sunday, securing their third consecutive win with a 112-110 victory.
Others: Harrison Barnes stepped up for the Spurs during the second quarter, finishing the half with 15 points.
Devin Vassell and Keldon Johnson led the Spurs' rally in the third quarter.
Julius Randle chipped in 16 points for the Timberwolves.
Anthony Edwards scored 14 points for Minnesota.
